{"word":"ἀναβάλλω","slug":"ἀναβάλλω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>ἀναβάλλω</el></b> [<el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἀνά\">ἀνά</a>, <a class=\"S\" href=\"S:βάλλω\">βάλλω</a></el>] in the one use of <el>ἀ.</el> in the <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ NT\">NT</a>, <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ mid.\">mid.</a> <el>ἀναβάλλομαι</el> (also the more common voice in older Greek): <b><i>defer, put off, postpone:</i></b> with <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ acc.\">acc.</a> of the <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ pers.\">pers.</a> affected <el>ἀνεβάλετο αὐτούς</el> <i>he put them off</i> = <i>adjourned their hearing</i> (a legal <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ t.t.\">t.t.</a>) <b><a href='B:510 24:22'>Ac 24:22</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:ἀναβαίνω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:ἀναβέβηκα\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}